    <h1>BADMITON : My favourite sport</h1>
    <h2>My story with Badminton</h2>
    I have been playing badminton for the past <i>5 years</i>.<br>
    The badminton classes I joined was <mark>Victor Badminton Academy</mark>.<br>
    Achieved <strong>Winners</strong> and <strong>Runners up</strong> positions.<br>
    <h3>Advantages of Badminton</h3>
    <p>
        Badminton improves <q>muscles strength, heart functioning, flexibility</q>. It offers the <q>perfect balance of physical and mental challenges</q>. It's fast-paced, exciting, and offers endless opportunities for improvement. Playing badminton is not just good for physical fitness, but also for mental well-being, <i>it's a great stress buster.</i>
    </p>
    <h3>Disadvantages of Badminton</h3>
    <p>
        <q>Badminton is not without risks</q>. Players can experience injuries such as sprains. While basic badminton equipment is <strong>affordable</strong>, quality racquets, shoes, and other accessories can be <strong>relatively expensive</strong>, <q>especially for competitive players</q>. While competition can be motivating, it may also lead to stress and anxiety for players, particularly young athletes.
    </p>
    <mark>In conclusion, Badminton has been a <sup>very</sup> part of my life.</mark>

